2500|$|In 2012, Senator Brown {{urged the}} Department of Defense {{to comply with}} a rule that {{requires}} military service members to wear clothes and boots made in the U.S. rather than in China. [...] "If it's taxpayer dollars, it should help American workers and American businesses, pure and simple. Our men and <b>women</b> <b>in</b> <b>uniform</b> are fighting for their country, and deserve to fight in quality uniforms and boots that are made in the U.S.A." [...] Brown said.|$|E
