50|$|Merry-Go-Round {{is a large}} oil {{on canvas}} {{painting}} made by Mark Gertler in 1916, when he was 24 years old. It is perhaps his most famous work, and depicts men and <b>women</b> (many <b>in</b> <b>uniform)</b> on a merry-go-round ride. The painting (and another 1915 painting entitled Swing Boats, now lost) may {{have been inspired by}} a ride at the annual fair on Hampstead Heath.|$|R
